Functions for selecting attributes from a given dataset. Attribute subset selection is the process of identifying and removing as much of the irrelevant and redundant information as possible.

name: r-fselector
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.34" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-fselector
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/FSelector_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/FSelector/FSelector_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 29d16e4acb266d91c4648dfa36d416ca522b0c18327d5b6e3c9a7e93a777db1e

build:
  number: 2
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rweka
    - r-digest
    - r-entropy
    - r-randomforest
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rweka
    - r-digest
    - r-entropy
    - r-randomforest

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('FSelector')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('FSelector')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=FSelector
  license: GPL-2.0-only
  summary: Functions for selecting attributes from a given dataset. Attribute subset selection is the process of identifying and removing as much of the irrelevant and redundant information as possible.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
